resource.string: "#####&#000a;# walkable stage, with floor tilemap and input handling for clicks&#000a;&#000a;extends Node2D&#000a;&#000a;var scene&#000a;var player&#000a;&#000a;var body_layer&#000a;var nav&#000a;var tiles&#000a;var outline&#000a;var movement_allowed = true&#000a;var utils = preload("res://scripts/utils.gd").new()&#000a;&#000a;const TILE_ATTRACT = 7&#000a;const TILE_TRANSITION = 0&#000a;&#000a;# shortcut for checking which tile type is at (x,y)&#000a;func tile_at(point):&#000a; var map_point = tiles.world_to_map(point)&#000a; var tile_id = tiles.get_cell(map_point.x, map_point.y)&#000a; return tile_id&#000a;&#000a;# helper for checking all tiles adjacent to the one at a given point&#000a;func get_surrounding_tiles(point):&#000a; var map_pos = tiles.world_to_map(point)&#000a; var NW = tiles.get_cell(map_pos.x-1, map_pos.y)&#000a; var NE = tiles.get_cell(map_pos.x, map_pos.y-1)&#000a; var SE = tiles.get_cell(map_pos.x+1, map_pos.y)&#000a; var SW = tiles.get_cell(map_pos.x, map_pos.y+1)&#000a; return Array([NW, NE, SE, SW])&#000a;&#000a;func check_for_attractor(point):&#000a; var borders = get_surrounding_tiles(point)&#000a; if( borders[0] == TILE_ATTRACT ):&#000a; return "NW"&#000a; elif( borders[1] == TILE_ATTRACT ):&#000a; return "NE"&#000a; elif( borders[2] == TILE_ATTRACT ):&#000a; return "SE"&#000a; elif( borders[3] == TILE_ATTRACT ):&#000a; return "SW"&#000a; else:&#000a; return null&#000a; &#000a;&#000a;func check_for_transition(point):&#000a; return ( tile_at(point) == TILE_TRANSITION )&#000a;&#000a;func _unhandled_input(ev):&#000a;&#000a; # Move character around on click&#000a; if (ev.type == InputEvent.MOUSE_BUTTON and ev.pressed and ev.button_index==1):&#000a; &#000a; &#000a; &#000a; var begin = player.get_global_pos()&#000a; &#000a; # This massive chunk of code cancels out the effects of the camera&#000a; # on our positioning calculations&#000a; var end = get_viewport_transform().affine_inverse().xform( ev.global_pos )&#000a; &#000a; # Flag used mostly for placement of the outline&#000a; var adjust_path = false&#000a; &#000a; # Find the closest tile center to where we clicked&#000a; var tilepos = tiles.world_to_map(end)&#000a; var mappos = tiles.map_to_world(tilepos)&#000a; end = mappos + Vector2(0, 18) &#000a; &#000a; # Store which type of tile is at that point&#000a; var tile_at = tiles.get_cell(tilepos.x, tilepos.y)&#000a; &#000a; # if the player clicked an un-walkable tile,&#000a; # we'll remove the end point from the calculated path&#000a; # so the targeting outline shows where it will really end up&#000a; if ( tiles.get_tileset().tile_get_navigation_polygon(tile_at) == null ):&#000a; adjust_path = true&#000a; &#000a; &#000a; &#000a; if( movement_allowed ):&#000a; player.update_path(begin, end, nav);&#000a; outline.show()&#000a; &#000a; if( adjust_path ):&#000a; outline.set_global_pos(player.path[1])&#000a; player.path[0] = player.path[1]&#000a; else:&#000a; outline.set_global_pos(end)&#000a; &#000a; if( ev.meta == 1 ):&#000a; outline.hide()&#000a; &#000a; yield(player, "done_moving")&#000a; outline.hide()&#000a; get_surrounding_tiles(player.get_global_pos())&#000a; &#000a; var orient = check_for_attractor(player.get_global_pos())&#000a; if( not orient == null ):&#000a; player.orient(orient)&#000a; &#000a; &#000a; var transitioning = check_for_transition(player.get_global_pos())&#000a; if( transitioning == true ):&#000a; utils.goto_scene("res://main.xml", {})&#000a; &#000a; &#000a;func _ready():&#000a; # Setup the vars and conditions for this instance&#000a; scene = get_node("/root/scene")&#000a; player = scene.get("player")&#000a; &#000a; body_layer = get_node("nav/floor/bodies")&#000a; nav = get_node("nav")&#000a; tiles = get_node("nav/floor")&#000a; outline = get_node("destination_sprite")&#000a; utils = get_node("/root/utils")&#000a; &#000a; outline.hide()&#000a; set_process_unhandled_input(true)&#000a;"

"&#000a;extends YSort&#000a;&#000a;# member variables here, example:&#000a;# var a=2&#000a;# var b="textvar"&#000a;&#000a;func _ready():&#000a; add_user_signal("player_redirected", ["successful", "expected", "actual"])&#000a; # Initialization here&#000a; pass&#000a;&#000a;&#000a;"

"extends Camera2D&#000a;const REF_HEIGHT = 600 #basis&#000a;var zoom = 1 # lower = zoomed in&#000a;&#000a;func _ready():&#000a; get_viewport().connect("size_changed", self, "adjust_zoom")&#000a; adjust_zoom()&#000a;&#000a;func adjust_zoom():&#000a; var screen = get_tree().get_root().get_rect().size&#000a; var width = screen.x&#000a; var height = screen.y&#000a; var ratio = width / height&#000a; var zoom = (REF_HEIGHT * ratio / width) * self.zoom&#000a; set_zoom( Vector2(zoom, zoom) )&#000a;&#000a;"

"extends Node&#000a;&#000a;var quests = []&#000a;var active_quests&#000a;var quests_ready = false&#000a;&#000a;signal quests_loaded&#000a;&#000a;func get_state(quest, state):&#000a; if not ( has_node(quest) ):&#000a; print("Error - no such quest to update")&#000a; return null&#000a; return get_node(quest).current_state&#000a;&#000a;func set_state(quest, state):&#000a; get_node(quest).set_current_state(state)&#000a; &#000a;&#000a;func _quests_ready():&#000a; var ret = false&#000a; for quest in quests:&#000a; if( quest.is_attached() == true ):&#000a; continue&#000a; else:&#000a; return false&#000a; return true&#000a;&#000a;&#000a;func _fixed_process(delta):&#000a; if( quests_ready == false ):&#000a; if( _quests_ready() == true ):&#000a; emit_signal("quests_loaded")&#000a; quests_ready = true&#000a; #set_fixed_process(false)&#000a;&#000a;func _ready():&#000a; #add_user_signal("quests_loaded")&#000a; quests = get_children()&#000a;&#000a; set_fixed_process(true)&#000a;&#000a;&#000a;"
